that I get too much kashk if I eat too much food, especially cheese. This led to acid reflux, which is always inconvenient but worse especially at night. Fun fact: you can totally feel the parietal cells of your stomach, even if they’re not directly accessible. If I took antacids, the effect came like a drip from below, or 7-8 hours after medication. If I took it with a meal, or just before bed/after a big meal, the magic happened fast.

Top-down vs bottom-up, mainstream vs. empiricism, validation vs. authorship: this is the problem I’ve never quite envisioned a successful solution for. Six years of post-undergrad work and not a single lead. I was certainly interested in the topic and applied the whole RCT thing anyway simply because I am interested in everything as much as I dislike everything. I’m trapped.
